description: 1936. In the midst of a Europe which has been at peace for 75 years, a new city ermerges unlike any other in the world: Metropolis, the capital of excess and urban delirium. It is the focal point of numerous political movements and artistic trends as well as the nerve center for various forms of espionage and other underhanded activities. The citizens of Metropolis speak of nothing else but the horrible crimes plaguing the poorest parts of the city. To solve these crimes, the police have called upon an Austrian doctor, the inventor of a little-known field of science involving the treatment of the mind: a certain Doctor Freud.
name: Volume 1

description: NAMELESS tells the story of a down-at-heel occult hustler known only as "Nameless" who is recruited by a consortium of billionaire futurists as part of a desperate mission to save the world. A massive asteroid named Xibalba—the "Place of Fear" in Mayan mythology—is on collision course with the planet Earth. If that wasn't trouble enough, the asteroid has an enormous magical symbol carved into its side and is revealed to be a fragment of our solar system's lost fifth planet, Marduk, destroyed sixty-five million years ago at the end of an epic cosmic war between the inhabitants of Marduk and immensely powerful, life-hating, extra-dimensional "gods." One of those beings is still alive, imprisoned on Xibalba, dreaming of its ultimate revenge on all that exists. When Nameless and his teammates inadvertently unleash this malignant soul-destroying intelligence, the stage is set for a nightmarish, nihilistic journey to the outer reaches of human terror.
name: HC/TPB

description: Mr. Rhee... in the future... in space. Yes... RHEE-ly... but nothing is quite as it seems in this dramatic conclusion to TALES OF MR. RHEE Volume 3!

volume.name: Tales of Mr. Rhee: Those Who Fight Monsters...
Princess of Power: A Born Champion
Die Abenteuer von Tanguy und Laverdure

name: Robin Hood and the Scarlet Sentinel

description:
Story Titles

  • Eine Ladung Aprilfische
  • Der Lenz ist da!
  • Legende vom Ostermann
  • Ferienhotel für Pflanzengäste
  • Geschichten vom Hof: Omas Superkuh Käthe
  • Kampf um das Licht
  • Das Wettschießen
  • Bildung tut not
  • Gegen die „Tyrannei“ der Jahreszeiten
  • Auf der Suche nach dem Frühling
  • April, April
  • Zwischen Traum und Gaumenkitzel
  • Die Blume der Hoffnung
  • Im Land der Ostereier
  • Wieder was gespart...
  • Das Huhn mit den goldenen Eiern
name: Frohe Ostern

description:
Story Titles

  • Missglückte Osterüberraschung
  • Ein lästiges Osterei
  • Musterschüler mit Schurkendiplom
  • Unvergessliches Frühlingsfest
  • Der verhexte Doppelgänger
  • Zauber des Frühlings
  • Fragwürdiger Ersatz
  • Zum Hasen gemacht
  • Rätsel um das Riesenei
  • Ab auf die Osterinsel!
  • Die Blumen des Bösen
  • Erfrischend anders...
name: Frohe Ostern

description:
Welcome back from the flashback nightmare that was Detective Tuesday's past! The previous issue was just small glimpse into her coming into this world for the second time.

This issue is full of surprises! Find out how Robert The Doll, Detective Tuesday and Officer Pigstein learn the truth behind what happened to Stan the Goatman! How do they find out? Start reading now!

Nightmare?

Alex Cooper falls into the dream world of Comatose, a world that is part dream, part game; full of action, adventure, and blood thirsty monsters. With the help of his friend Kevin he begins to make his escape from this world, but they soon discover that there is more to this world than meets the eye. Follow Kevin and Alex and their adventures in Comatose.

Chapter 4: Nightmare?

Alex makes his escape from Comatose, but discovers that all is not well in the real world when he awakens.
name: Nightmare?

description:
Blood Sisters

Ember Keane wakes to sirens, warning of a Revenant presence in the city of Solice. She meets up with her sister, Taymar, who wants to get a closer look on the deadly creature.
name: Blood Sisters

description: As Sister Long becomes better friends with her new companion, the two of them learn a great deal about Japanese culture and how to teach the people with love and hope. Sister Long even starts teaching a Chinese woman and experiences a change in perspective.
name: Month 10: November

volume.name: DENDO: One Year and One Half in Tokyo

description:
What is and What Should Never Be

The aftermath of last issue's events brings new information, emotions and changes to our heroes in the last issue of the first arc!
name: What Is and What Should Never Be

description: Rehema and Kwasi have settled into a new life in a village for men and women with albinism. Hidden from the outside world, young Kwasi grows healthy and strong. However, the infant hasn't been forgotten by the Witch Doctor and his flesh harvester, Majuto. Using all the power at their command, they hunt young Kwasi, for his white flesh is the key component of a powerful spell that just might lead to...resurrection...

What Makes A Hero? Part 2

Captain Delta is a fraud! But how? And what did Element see to make him think this? The shocking origin of Captain Delta is revealed!
name: What Makes A Hero? Part 2

description:
Batter Up!

Our three heroes finally meet, but not as planned! More players present themselves, suggesting that there is a greater threat for them than the Mannequin!
name: Batter Up!

description:
Journey

Years after their expedition from the Factory, Sis and Bro have been taught the ways of the hunter by Dorje and his daughter Rinchen. They have found themselves a new home, joining the culture of the people outside the wall. It is now time for their people's annual festival at the holy city of Alsah.
name: Chapter Three: Journey

description:
The birth of a family's firstborn baby should be a reason to celebrate the miracle of life.

Unless you're Paulette Najera and find your brand new child the most hideous creature on the planet.

Can Taro, her son, grow up to be a kid full with self-confidence and the ability to realize his dreams?

We're guessing "no".
No one is as they seem in this adult coloring book themed issue.

A human girl is running for her life-right into Suki!

She wears foreign clothing from across the sea.

Will Suki choose to save the stranger?

It All Falls Down

Seeing the last Brujas true potential, Gruff has done the unthinkable and has unleashed the Three Jacks into the city with one goal, end Althalia Cabrera and anyone that calls her friend. Heck of a price to pay, but the job does come with full benefits and paid vacation. If she can survive to use it ...
name: It All Falls Down

description:
Frankenstein

In which Molly is whoa-ooh-oh-ooh-whoa caught in a bad (gothic) romance.
name: Frankenstein

description:
A Different Path

Things are looking good for our two heroes! They have a new friend in Glorm (a Shoal, what the?!?), Lloyd has an awesome new power suit and they're rescuing, like, loads of Burians!

It's sure a good thing that Bear met Lloyd and went on these adventures, uh? Now hey, do you think all Burians would have done the same thing....?
name: A Different Path

description:
Chapter 3: Invitation

Melchizedek and Evangeline go on their routine patrol of Grand City, but Mel has other plans: to meet Natural Selection.
name: Chapter 3: Invitation

description:
Static

The No Signal series continues with Part 2: Static, as Wally finds himself under the pressure of the media following the unveiling of the imagination translator. Meanwhile, news of a device in development sends Zach and Jen into a panic as they try to get the ‘old’ Wally back.
name: Static

description: Nobody Can Eat 50 Eggs #10 is simply crazy awesome. Or at least I think so. Featuring Horrible, Horrible Pet Products, Counterfeit Leaf Collection Books, When Ice Cream Ruled the World, and more!
The Owlgirls defend themselves as they are confronted by Don Amichee's thugs, which ends with a trip to the Coney Island boardwalk and an afternoon at the beach. Something smells fishy!

The Pride of the Chickenhawks

When a minor league baseball team called the Brisbane Chickenhawks is rocked by allegations of steroid use, Justice International private investigator Rob Hanes goes undercover on the ball club to investigate. However, Rob soon becomes more interested in trying to get on base than solve the case...
name: The Pride of the Chickenhawks

description: "The knowledge of our world revealed as usurped and abused, will we rise to our needed station or remain sheep forever herded?" Shepherd 11: 8-9

Pain and Compromises Part 2

The Rats make headway in their plans to capture the Seal of Iberion while the hunt turns out to be more difficult than expected for the Ravenwood cousins. Their own searches start uncovering secrets about the Earl Hadge's trading city - secrets that the Earl cannot afford to come to light. Meanwhile, when an operation to gather information at a local tavern goes terribly wrong, Pandora is left fighting for her life.
name: Pain and Compromises Part 3

description:
Imperium: Part 5

Alina and Velang face off in the arena, providing them an opportunity to carry out their plan. Zarran and Raver encounter one of the Wasteland tribes. Emperor Trovaar recalls Primus Plask from his mission in the Wastelands.
name: Imperium: Part 5

description:
Previously in Those Shadow People...

A portal connecting two worlds was destroyed with grave consequences for both worlds. Now, the citizens of Dark City work to deal with the fallout. Here's what happened next in the Shadow Realm...

The Rise of Unit 5

September 11, 2001 was an ominous day in U.S history. However, it became the turning point in the fight against global terror. Founded by the United States Government and born out of the personal tragedies of 5 extraordinary individuals. Each with deep ties to ground zero, the Unit 5 tactical anti-terror unit was born. Join the Unit 5 team on their next mission to Washington D.C. where they attempt to put a stop to a known terror threat. Fasten your seat belt and prepare to meet Tech's nemesis and new member of the terror group Negative 5 - Bubbles!
name: The Rise of Unit 5

description: In "Berserker", Casey's new haircut creates expected drama for Cynthia, and Jorge prepares himself for the fall-out of Melissa's article. In "The Good Child", Lynette takes care of an annoyance while Kano confronts his sister over a bad business decision.
name: Berserker; The Good Child

description:
The Ape-Man Cometh

POWER NELSON, the public-domain hero from the Golden Age of comics, wages war against a genocidal horde of Ape-Men on an alien world! But, are Nelson's extraordinary abilities enough to ensure victory when he is confronted with the added threat of the simian regime's mysterious ally, ALABASTOR STRANGEGNOME?
name: The Ape-Man Cometh

description:
"Beyond the wall is a goddess who was shackled by 700 of her siblings. In her prison she keeps a fluid garden of flowers which can bring the dead back to life. To get to her, a bargain will be struck for your body. You must walk amongst the fallen. Your sword must divide her jailer. None of these things are easy. Especially a second time."

Ashen, the most recent small-press release from cartoonist Chase Van Weerdhuizen, is the story of a woman who must journey beyond a grim wall at the edge of her world to try and save the life of her sister, though this time it may be futile.

In a Victorian steampunk world, monsters and creatures of the night are not going to fit in. Someone has to round them up and put them away. That's the job of the Big Game Hunters, a rag-tag band of Steampunk Victorian monster hunters with mad skills, blunderbusses and a nose for trouble. In their first complete 3-part adventure, they exterminate a creature in the Scottish Highlands only to discover their reward is a trip to a seemingly deserted Prussian village courtesy of their mysterious benefactor in the Queen's Directorate. All is not as it seems and the Lizard Baron threatens to stop the Big Game Hunters almost as soon as they've started.

Note: The digital edition (3/9/2016) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Big Game Hunters: The Tale of the Lizard Baron

description:
Contagion

Playing their largest concert in their hometown, metal band and reformed monster hunters "Subliminal Torment" and their fans are attacked by the worst creatures they've ever faced. After the monsters slaughter the fans in homage to a previous encounter, the band is left to take the fall.
name: Contagion

description: These legendary stories, from the classic first fifteen issues of Bagge's Hate comic, are a defining icon of Seattle's early 1990s culture, as well as Generation X in general. This is the first time these hilarious stories, starring the hapless Buddy Bradley and his cast of loser cohorts, have ever been available under one cover, and never have they been available at such a low price! Bagge's riotous tales of the early 1990s subculture are more hilarious now than ever, and find out why he has been praised by R. Crumb, Matt Groening, John Kricfalusi, Publishers Weekly, Entertainment Weekly and many more as a comedy genius.
name: Volume 1

description:
Rising From The Grave

Cartoonist Jay P. Fosgitt (Marvel, IDW, Red5) returns to his darkly humorous roots with his diminutive version of Death and his sidekick, the sexy Zombie Chick.
name: Rising From The Grave

description:
THE SAMANDURAN

To uncover the mysterious schemes of ancient Samanduran cult, young Inspector Devon Horne of the Constabulary's Arcane Affairs, enlists the aid of Everard Rook, one of world's the last practicing sorcerers.
name: The Samanduran

description:
Collects Electromagnate #1 - 8 plus adds many pages.

A dark cabal has usurped the designs of Nikola Tesla's and built a global relay grid of electromagnetic towers. The structured data streams of this new matrix are as ubiquitous as oxygen.

Before the conspirators can make everyone's reliance on the data they control as vital as the biological need for oxygen, a final piece is needed. The relay circuit must be closed for the illusions of the data blanket to be complete.

A single tower, on the tiny island nation of Malta, in the center of the Mediterranean Sea, is the last obstacle preventing the villains from deceiving the entire world.
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Electromagnate: The Book of Rebel Nations

description: This issue sees the GalaXafreaks battle the evil King Freak. Watch the trans dimensional super-hero Captain Yeah! get into a spot of bother thanks to two of his biggest fans!
Silveo is a teenaged assassin. He's small and pretty, and he always gets his target. This time, though, he's in way over his head.

volume.name: The Guild of the Cowry Catchers

description: Hex Of the Wicked Witch is set in a futuristic decayed Salem Massachusetts the city is dark and culminated by evil. Witches, vampires, werewolves and voodoo priests fight an endless battle for control of the city. The Wicked Witch belonged to a coven that was recently murdered. Only she has survived. Rumor has it that in Hell, the souls of these witches are being held captive and their power being harnessed to some warlock back on earth. The Wicked Witch must find this warlock and destroy him before his power allows him to take control of Salem. But time is running out as the witches and warlocks of Salem are battling each other for control of the city. Can the Wicked Witch save the city or is it destined to destroy itself? Also includes special sketchbook section.
The bullying is out of control. Lester is on the bridge facing his destiny - the #will he jump? hashtag trending. But something doesn't go exactly as planned ... who or what saves him?
name: Vol. 1

description:
Chapter I

Houndstooth follows the adventures of Bandit, an orphaned boy who exists in an animal's world, along with his fellow human and best friend, Pan. The only adventure Bandit has ever wanted to have, are the ones printed inside his favorite books. But, fate brought an unwanted adventure to his feet when Pan is kidnapped! Her only hope of rescue is Bandit and a couple of unlikey tag-alongs.
name: Chapter I

description:
YONKS in the making!

FULL COLOUR! (Mainly blue)

If you loved Hutcho's 'Walking to Japan', 'Lesson Master', 'Tales from the Pub', and 'You Stink and I Don't'...

OR

You're just a big fan of musical warriors - then this comic needs to be in your weird, sweaty mitts... PRONTO!

The Iron Bard, a mysterious minstrel barbarian, battles through waves of attackers, using a unique blend of violence and song.

You won't believe page 16! (Just joking! That page sucks)

With Hutching's eyeball stroking attention to detail, and musical scores woven into the panels, this epic comic will make you will feel like you're immersed in an eXtreme screen cinematic assault of hilarity.

First Contact

A fallen warrior, Firefox, falls to earth and finds a unwilling John Kirby to merge with to help save his planet from Omega Doma, and stop her from collecting all the 8th Waves.
name: First Contact

description: Family, Country and the Bushido code is what has kept Mariachi alive. The lone escapee of a devastating family massacre, at the age of 10 he fled his beloved Mexico to survive. Toshiro Yasumori, took him to Japan to fulfill his oath and protect the boy at all cost. A supernatural force of tremendous power has destroyed everything they had and now they are the last remaining witnesses of such diabolic threat.
name: Vol. 2

description:
Encounters

Jack, a shy, tortured young man, hooks up with a mysterious stranger at a bar and loses himself in an intense and exhilarating night with him in his hotel room, during which he sees visions of bloodshed and ancient gods. In the morning, he discovers he's been branded with a mysterious tattoo-the one his mysterious stranger had-and is now imbued with dark and brutal powers. But will those powers be enough to save him from a vicious gang attack?

This digital edition includes 45 pages of bonus features including promotional art, earlier versions of full pages, and the evolution of "The Mark"!
name: Encounters

description: A house cat has a job interview and later saves his boyfriend (a dog) from a kidnapping.

Five left-of-the-dial, music-obsessed teens struggle through the rise and fall of Generation X and the Alternative Rock era of the 1990s. They learn that the bonds of friendship they thought were unbreakable have already begun to crack, and the music they thought they'd love forever has already started to fade.

FOR FANS OF: Love & Rockets, Ghost World, Craig Thompson's Blankets
name: Collected Edition

description: MOTH is the story of Anime-obsessed Sebastian and art-freak Claryssa as they awkwardly navigate the cruel social hierarchy of high school. A horrific event on the school's athletic field threatens their friendship and sends Sebastian on an apocalyptic mission, whereby fantasy and reality intermingle with dangerous consequences. Written with dark wit that's ultimately after your heart, MOTH is an exploration of friendship, adolescence, loss, and mental illness.

This single-issue story follows Billy, a young man estranged from his family. Billy heads home one day after years away, hoping to make amends. But when he gets there, he discovers that he is too late: his family is dead. They've been murdered. He doesn't know by whom, and he doesn't know why, but he does know that he's the only one left now to see things put right. It's up to him to give his family the memorial they deserve.

It Takes 4 to F*ck

Before Revenger was roaming the country exacting vengeance for the poor and down-trodden, she ran with a group of rough kids called The Fog. Based out of Southern California in the late 70s, The Fog like taking on meth-dealing bikers and taking back neighborhoods for the people. But one member of the Fog has a Father. A Father who wants her little girl to be a star. What lengths will he go to make that happen? Find out here in the first of 4 issues.
name: It Takes 4 to F*ck

person_credits.name: Charles Forsman
person_credits.role: writer, artist, letterer, colorist, cover, production

description: This unique full color 24 page anthology collects strange stories of Robots, written BY children. These unique perspectives reveal laughter, action, and an overall sense of hope. The imaginative world of children is on display!

When a troubled boy discovers his father works for The Zoom Family of armored heroes, can he turn his life around and become a hero by hanging out with some of the best?

Katsumi Darian, AKA Rocket Queen, enlists Jamie, the son of Zoom Family armourer, to help find her mother's killer. Jamie is about to find out what happens when his curiosity gets the better of him and he needs some armored help! Meanwhile, the costumed psychopath Alpha is trying to kill them!
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Rocket Queen and the Wrench: Acting Out

description:
Waking up in a field, the thing that used to be known as Dwight Cochran rises. His memories vague, his body weak, he finds strength and lucidity after 'feeding', stealing the life force of living things through prehensile dead tissues in his hair and nails. His memories return... of his work as a contract killer, his time on death row, his terminal cancer, and his zealous faith.

When a maniacal government scientist performed experiments on Cochran for the military... What did they create? And how much destruction will their creation leave in its wake?

Creature Feature

Welcome to The Showdown! In the first issue, we meet the first groups of creatures vying for the win in the great race through hell. There is plenty of gasoline and gore as The Showdown gets underway.

Slingers One

Welcome to the Swinging Sixties...

A.D. 2963

SLINGERS is science-fiction adventure with a sixties aesthetic. The Rat Pack in space. DM and Frank are two wartime buddies now trying to make their way in a post-war world. DM is staying out of trouble for the sake of his fiancée, Jeannie, but Frank is finding it harder to stay on the straight and narrow. Despite their best intentions, they are about to be set on a new path where trouble finds them...

London 2105. When Lance Hendrix and his team are called upon to do a routine soul transfer all may not be as it seems. Who is their mysterious subject with the dark soul, why is he being hunted by the authorities and what does the devious Draxman have to do with the stranger and Hendrix’s past? The Soul Trader’s story begins.

Monster

Jack is new to the town of Manitou Valley, Maine. His optimistic dad works at the mysterious Maltox Factory making who-knows-what. When a monster wreaks havoc in the sleepy town, the towns-people blame the wood-creature known as the Wendigo, but Jack suspects it may be something else.

Part of a series of stories from creators Larry Fessenden, James Felix McKenney and Brahm Revel.
name: Monster

description:
Goddess of War

Dissatisfied as a showgirl and rich man's mistress, Sophia Fulbright wants something more. After receiving a fan letter from a love-struck RFC pilot, Sophie begins a correspondence that dares her to dream of a happier life. Set in 1918, in the midst of a power struggle between theater and film, Goddess of War is the story of a Lost Generation youth coming to terms with the harsh realities of life.
name: Goddess of War

description:
Before Anyone Else

Hazel and Laurel are best friends.They are each others Bae. When the zombie apocalypse hits Malibu, it threatens their friendship. But Hazel is not going to let a little thing like a zombie bite keep her away from spending time with her bestie.
name: Before Anyone Else

description: Celebrate the 75th anniversary of Archie Comics with this special retrospective presentation! When Josie first got her own title, she and Melody hadn't started the famous band yet! It wasn't until #45 of the series that they met Valerie and donned their long tails and ears for hats. From there, the all-girl rock band catapulted into super-stardom, becoming one of the most beloved Archie franchises of all time! In this collection, we'll take a look at the entire 106-issue series and their lives both on and off the stage!
name: Josie and the Pussycats

description: Edel Nacht's Titan threatens to destroy all of London. With one Bombshell down, will another one be forced to sacrifice her own life?
name: The Battle of Britain Part 5 of 6

description: Wonder Woman has been making a big splash in the European Theater of Operations, and it’s drawn the notice of Nazi high command-and something even scarier!
name: Chapter Nineteen

deck: A subtle blend of science fiction, comedy and action, you'll soon fall in love with the dynamism and charisma of Tessa intergalactic agent!
description:
Tessa is a bubbly schoolgirl of 16. She loves her family, friends, studying and gymnastics competitions. But then, one night an alien materializes in the middle of her room!

Tessa finds herself teleported millions of light years from Earth. Her presence is required by the highest authorities of the universe to become the 42th and last Intergalactic Agent.
name: Sideral Killer

deck: Tessa, the dynamic young lady, has been given her first official mission.
description:
Tessa and Swidz wash up on T-zhé, the famous "asteroid maze" that no one has managed to leave from hundreds of millions of years, in order to escort a Hou-Brihan diplomat to the planet Liwou Wo-2.

Tessa will encounter mercenaries obsessed with searching for fabulous treasure, creatures there in spite of themselves, and the "Reaper" who is lurking in the heart of the asteroid ready to do away with all those who approach its territory.
name: Les Dix Dalles du Labyrinthe

deck: Tessa meets Diyo, a charming alien who has fallen madly in love with her. Will Tessa share his feelings?
description:
As always, Tessa is late for school. She decides to shortcut through her neighbor Mr. Koaffar's house. In Mr. Koaffar's basement Tessa discovers a very unusual machine that transports both she and Mr. Koaffar to an industrial town. Mr. Koaffar seems to know the place and one person in particular.

Tessa meets Swidz and Diyo who offers to become "her guide, in this day and for centuries to come." Confused, Tessa accepts, unaware that this is equivalent to a marriage proposal...
name: Beau Comme un Diyo

description:
Tessa is honored to participate in the 290,376th Cosmolympiades, the famous concept of games created and marketed by a gang named Zeus.

Throughout 12 perilous trials, Tessa will have to compete with six other same rank officers.

But what she does not suspect is that a terrible threat hangs over the games... the Sidereal Killer!
name: Cosmolympiades

deck: A new danger-fraught adventure lies in store for Tessa!
description: What are Gemmes?... Micro-universes where the most fearsome psychopaths are sent. The problem is that Tessa has managed to get herself locked up in one of them along with her mentor Swidz and the entire Pi-Youx people! Hell doesn't even begin to describe what awaits them...
name: Où il y a de la gemme...

deck: A new adventure featuring the most famous and hectic intergalactic agent!
description: Tessa against Atalanta?!
name: Aurore Montréal

deck: The conclusion of the adventures of the most famous intergalactic agent!
description:
Why would Swidz, Tessa's mentor and confidant, pull a gun on Tessa? Is his brain twisted or is he suffering from a fever of unknown alien origin?

No, the truth revealed in this latest installment of the saga, is much more terrible. The masks will finally be removed!

Grhamm, Nitaar, Djébriil, Ari, the Gods of Olympus, nubuck, the Pluriconsulat, will be united. And while the former allies become bitter enemies, Tessa will have the opportunity to kill the Sidereal Killer ... Will she destroy that which, for millennia, devastated the ranks of the Intergalactic Agents? One thing is certain: after their meeting, nothing will ever be the same!
name: Les Visions de l'Av'Eugg
